OL,3,CDevon MPs call for u-turn on axing of
OL,4,C#50 South West Water bill subsidy
OL,6,FDevon's Conservative MPs are asking
OL,7,Fthe government to reverse its decision
OL,8,Fto end the yearly #50 contribution to
OL,9,FSouth West Water customers' bills.
OL,11,FThe annual subsidy was first
OL,12,Fintroduced in 2013 to help bill payers
OL,13,Fin the region, where water bills were
OL,14,Fsignificantly higher than the national
OL,15,Faverage.
OL,17,FIt was due to end on 31 March 2025 and
OL,18,Fearlier this month the new Labour
OL,19,Fgovernment confirmed it will not be
OL,20,Fextending the government contribution
OL,21,Fto bills beyond this date.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
